Package de.ueberdosis.mp3info.id3v2

Interface Summary
DataSource Definition for a source of data
EncDescValFrame A very simple interface to mark frames.
 

Class Summary
ExtendedHeader Contains data about an extended header See the ID3V2 documentation.

Much to be done!
FileFrameDataSource A DataSource for frames that are read from a file.
FrameAENC Audio encryption This frame indicates if the actual audio stream is encrypted, and by whom.
FrameAPIC Attached Picture frame This frame contains a picture directly related to the audio file.
FrameCOMM Comments frame This frame is indended for any kind of full text information that does not fit in any other frame.
FrameCOMR Commercial frame This frame enables several competing offers in the same tag by bundling all needed information.
FrameENCR Encryption method registration To identify with which method a frame has been encrypted the encryption method must be registered in the tag with this frame.
FrameEQUA Equalisation Frame This is another subjective, alignment frame.
FrameETCO Event timing codes frame This frame allows synchronisation with key events in a song or sound.
FrameGEOB General encapsulated object In this frame any type of file can be encapsulated.
FrameIPLS Involved people frame Since there might be a lot of people contributing to an audio file in various ways, such as musicians and technicians, the 'Text information frames' are often insufficient to list everyone involved in a project.
FrameMCDI Music CD identifier frame This frame is intended for music that comes from a CD, so that the CD can be identified in databases such as the CDDB.
FrameOWNE Ownership frame The ownership frame might be used as a reminder of a made transaction or, if signed, as proof.
FramePCNT Play counter This is simply a counter of the number of times a file has been played.
FramePOPM Popularimeter The purpose of this frame is to specify how good an audio file is.
FramePOSS Position synchronisation frame This frame delivers information to the listener of how far into the audio stream he picked up; in effect, it states the time offset of the first frame in the stream.
FrameRBUF Recommended buffer size Sometimes the server from which a audio file is streamed is aware of transmission or coding problems resulting in interruptions in the audio stream.
FrameRVRB Reverb frame Yet another subjective one.
FrameSYLT Sychronised lyrics/text transcription
FrameSYTC Synchronised tempo codes For a more accurate description of the tempo of a musical piece this frame might be used.
FrameT Base class for all text related frames.
FrameTALB Album/Movie/Show title frame
FrameTBPM BPM frame
FrameTCOM Composer frame
FrameTCON Content type frame
FrameTCOP Copyright frame
FrameTDAT Date frame
FrameTDLY Playlist delay frame The 'Playlist delay' defines the numbers of milliseconds of silence between every song in a playlist.
FrameTENC Encoded by Frame.
FrameTEXT Textwriter Frame.
FrameTFLT Filetype Frame.
FrameTIME Time Frame.
FrameTIT1 Title 1 Frame.
FrameTIT2 Title/Songname/Content description frame
FrameTIT3 Title 3 Frame.
FrameTKEY Initial key Frame.
FrameTLAN Language Frame.
FrameTLEN Length Frame.
FrameTMED Media Frame The 'Media type' frame describes from which media the sound originated.
FrameTOAL Original album/movie/show title Frame The 'Original album/movie/show title' frame is intended for the title of the original recording (or source of sound), if for example the music in the file should be a cover of a previously released song.
FrameTOFN Original file name Frame The 'Original filename' frame contains the preferred filename for the file, since some media doesn't allow the desired length of the filename.
FrameTOLY Original lyricist Frame The 'Original lyricist(s)/text writer(s)' frame is intended for the text writer(s) of the original recording, if for example the music in the file should be a cover of a previously released song.
FrameTOPE Original artist(s)/performer(s)
FrameTORY Original release year Frame The 'Original release year' frame is intended for the year when the original recording, if for example the music in the file should be a cover of a previously released song, was released.
FrameTOWN File owner Frame The 'File owner/licensee' frame contains the name of the owner or licensee of the file and it's contents.
FrameTPE1 Lead artist(s)/Lead performer(s)/Soloist(s)/Performing group frame
FrameTPE2 Band Frame The 'Band/Orchestra/Accompaniment' frame is used for additional information about the performers in the recording.
FrameTPE3 Band Frame The 'Band/Orchestra/Accompaniment' frame is used for additional information about the performers in the recording.
FrameTPE4 Interpreter Frame The 'Interpreted, remixed, or otherwise modified by' frame contains more information about the people behind a remix and similar interpretations of another existing piece.
FrameTPOS Part of a set Frame The 'Part of a set' frame is a numeric string that describes which part of a set the audio came from.
FrameTPUB Publisher Frame The 'Publisher' frame simply contains the name of the label or publisher.
FrameTRCK Track frame The 'Track number/Position in set' frame is a numeric string containing the order number of the audio-file on its original recording.
FrameTRDA Recording date frame The 'Recording dates' frame is a intended to be used as complement to the "TYER", "TDAT" and "TIME" frames.
FrameTRSN Inet radio station frame The 'Internet radio station name' frame contains the name of the internet radio station from which the audio is streamed.
FrameTRSO Inet radio station owner frame The 'Internet radio station owner' frame contains the name of the owner of the internet radio station from which the audio is streamed.
FrameTSIZ Size frame The 'Size' frame contains the size of the audiofile in bytes, excluding the ID3v2 tag, represented as a numeric string.
FrameTSRC ISRC frame The 'ISRC' frame should contain the International Standard Recording Code (ISRC) (12 characters).
FrameTSSE Soft-/Hardwaresettings frame The 'Software/Hardware and settings used for encoding' frame includes the used audio encoder and its settings when the file was encoded.
FrameTXXX User defined text frame This frame is intended for one-string text information concerning the audiofile in a similar way to the other "T"-frames.
FrameTYER Year frame The 'Year' frame is a numeric string with a year of the recording.
FrameUFID Unique file identifier frame
FrameUSER Terms of use frame This frame contains a brief description of the terms of use and ownership of the file.
FrameUSLT Unsychronised lyrics/text transcription This frame contains the lyrics of the song or a text transcription of other vocal activities.
FrameW Base class for all URL frames (W000-WZZZ).
FrameWCOM Commercial url frame The 'Commercial information' frame is a URL pointing at a webpage with information such as where the album can be bought.
FrameWCOP Copyright url frame The 'Copyright/Legal information' frame is a URL pointing at a webpage where the terms of use and ownership of the file is described.
FrameWOAF Oficial audio url frame The 'Official audio file webpage' frame is a URL pointing at a file specific webpage.
FrameWOAR Oficial artist url frame The 'Official artist/performer webpage' frame is a URL pointing at the artists official webpage.
FrameWOAS Oficial audio source url frame The 'Official audio source webpage' frame is a URL pointing at the official webpage for the source of the audio file, e.g.
FrameWORS Oficial internet radio station url frame The 'Official internet radio station homepage' contains a URL pointing at the homepage of the internet radio station.
FrameWPAY Payment url frame The 'Payment' frame is a URL pointing at a webpage that will handle the process of paying for this file.
FrameWPUB Publisher url frame The 'Publishers official webpage' frame is a URL pointing at the official wepage for the publisher.
FrameWXXX User defined url frame This frame is intended for URL links concerning the audiofile in a similar way to the other "W"-frames.
Header  
Helper Provides some functionality that is necessary for decoding ID3v2
ID3V2Frame Contains information about one ID3v2 frame.
ID3V2Reader Contains all functionality to read and decode an ID3v2-Tag.
ID3V2Tag Contains the whole V2Tag.
ID3V2Writer The API for writing an ID3V2 tag to a file.
Languages Contains a list of all available (ISO 639-2) languages and a helper method
 

Exception Summary
NotAnID3V2FrameException  
SeekPastEndException Just a marker Exception so you know what happened.
